	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />At work we have servers which use both MediaWiki and <a href="http://twiki.org" class="postlink">TWiki</a>. Our IT guys are trying to migrate everything to TWiki; they claim it's more 'secure' or something. But i'd be happy to hear about anyone who had experience with both. TWiki seems a bit more powerful, but that might be just because i've used it more. But it also doesn't seem as fancy-looking.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

