<br />
<br />I totally agree. But i like when text is well-formatted and pleasing to the eye. Again, showing my bias only due to experience, TWiki makes it very easy to have a consistent text layout and flow with very little work. I'm sure MediaWiki is the same. Creating tables and headings and lists and outlines is dead-simple; it just works. And that's important on a project like this, collaborative and contribution-based.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
